Result.res10: Personality is, in fact, only a free being emphasizing and recognizing itself as such. Every man makes his own personality, he is to that extent his own creator.
Result.res11: The really valuable thing in the pageant of human life seems to me not the State but the creative, sentient individual, the personality; it alone creates the noble and the sublime, while the herd as such remains dull in thought and dull in feeling.
Result.res12: For the adult, all the world is a stage and the personality is the mask one wears to play the assigned role.
Result.res13: The largest part of what we call 'personality' is determined by how we've opted to defend ourselves against anxiety and sadness.
